Detailed Description

Structure of Ethernet flow data

The naming rules on Ethernet flows are as follows:


1. name="EMS";value="CompanyName/EMSname"

2. name="ManagedElement";value="ManagedElementName"

3. name="Flow";value="FlowName"

The format of FlowName is as follows:
"/rack=xx/shelf=yy/slot=zz/flow=nn"

globaldefs::NamingAttributes_T name:
The name of the Flow. This name must be unique networkwide and do not change with EMS upgrade.

string nativeEMSName:
The local name of the flow object. It is also the character string showed on T2000 interfaces.

string userLabel:
The user label of the flow object. It is also the character string showed on NMS interfaces.

string owner:
The owner of the flow object.

globaldefs::NamingAttributesList_T qosRuleNames:
The QoS rule list bound with the flow, including a CAR and a COS. The CAR and COS bound during flow creation are invalid. Bound QoS rules of a flow must be set using the "SetFlow" interface.

globaldefs::NVSList_T paraList:
Parameters of the flow, including the flow type, port ID, port type, VLAN ID, VB ID, and priority. The latter parameters vary with the flow type.

globaldefs::NVSList_T additionalInfo:
This attribute allows the communication from the EMS to the NMS of additional information which isn't explicitly modelled. It is a readonly attribute.
